---
/**
 * mistakes.astro — "What I got wrong" page. Postmortems of the failed/wrong calls.
 *
 * Why this page exists: a quant book that ships {quantProjectCount} winners and hides the
 * failure modes is a book primed for selection bias. A researcher's failures
 * are more diagnostic than their wins — they reveal what the discipline is
 * actually catching. This is the page that says "here is what my gates
 * stopped from shipping."
 *
 * Pattern: each entry is a real failure from one of the 9 quant projects
 * (or pre-research incidents), with: what was wrong, what the gate caught,
 * what I learned, what I changed in the pipeline.
 */
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Equation from '@components/Equation.astro';
import CTABanner from '@components/CTABanner.astro';
import { path } from '@utils/url';
import VoiceLine from '@components/VoiceLine.astro';
import { profile } from '@utils/profile';
import { countProjectsByRole } from '@utils/project-helpers';

// v6.10.42 — derive "n projects" claim from the canonical quant project count.
const quantProjectCount = await countProjectsByRole('quant');

// v6.10.47 — derive gate-count chrome from profile.stats.evalGates.
const GATE_RANGE = `G1–G${profile.stats.evalGates}`;

const mistakes = [
  {
    id: 'M01',
    title: 'Shipped a backtest with a 1-bar forward shift. Looked like a 5.07 Sharpe.',
    project: 'Project 09 — Look-ahead bias audit',
    date: '2026-06-18',
    severity: 'critical',
    summary:
      'While refactoring a momentum signal pipeline, I accidentally left a `.shift(-1)` on the signal column for two days. The "result" Sharpe was 5.07. The strategy was nonsense — every "trade" was using tomorrow\'s signal today.',
    caught_by: 'G21–G25 (look-ahead discipline, point-in-time verification)',
    repair:
      'Wrote project 09 as the canonical one-line shift test. The leaked-Sharpe was 5.07; the real Sharpe after removing the shift was 0.55. The phantom edge was 88% of the apparent alpha. The test now runs as a pre-ship gate on every backtest.',
    lesson:
      'A 5.07 Sharpe is not a feature. A 5.07 Sharpe that survives a one-line shift test is not, in fact, surviving — it is lying. The shift test is now mandatory. There is no "we\'ll just be careful next time."',
    formula: '\\text{phantom} = \\text{leaked} - \\text{real}',
  },
  {
    id: 'M02',
    title: 'In-sample Sharpe 0.91 in cross-sectional momentum. Out-of-sample Sharpe −0.03.',
    project: 'Project 02 — Cross-sectional momentum (18 coins)',
    date: '2025-10-15',
    severity: 'high',
    summary:
      '18 BTC-correlated altcoins, ranked by 14-day return, long top decile, short bottom decile. IS Sharpe 0.91. The OOS Sharpe was −0.03. Bootstrap CI [−0.12, +0.18] straddles zero — cannot reject the null.',
    caught_by: 'G11–G15 (locked OOS windows, pre-registration, frozen-spec evaluation)',
    repair:
      'Reported both numbers, side by side. The "honest decay" framing in the project writeup replaced what would have been a published-only-IS-Sharpe story. The bootstrap CI was reported with the bound, not as a one-sided significance test.',
    lesson:
      'Cross-sectional dispersion in a tightly-correlated universe (BTC-altcoin beta ≈ 1) is too small a signal to overcome rebalance friction at 14-day cadence. Project 05 (pairs via cointegration) is the *first* gate for stat-arb in this universe; cross-sectional momentum is downstream. The right order would have caught this earlier.',
    formula: '\\mathrm{CI}_{95\\%} \\ni 0 \\;\\Rightarrow\\; \\text{fail to reject null}',
  },
  {
    id: 'M03',
    title: 'BTC/ETH spread: looked like a textbook stat-arb. ADF said no.',
    project: 'Project 05 — Pairs via cointegration',
    date: '2026-02-18',
    severity: 'medium',
    summary:
      'BTC and ETH are the most obvious pair in crypto. The textbook trade is to hedge, fade the spread, collect mean-reversion. The ADF test statistic was −2.11. Critical value at 5% is ≈ −2.86. Spread has a unit root; the trade is not stationary. Half-life 208 days. OOS Sharpe ≈ 0.',
    caught_by: 'G1–G5 (mechanical validity), G6–G10 (statistical nulls)',
    repair:
      'Did not ship the trade. Shipped the rejection, with the ADF statistic and the half-life. The project is a published counter-example to the assumption "BTC and ETH are cointegrated."',
    lesson:
      "Stat-arb starts with the cointegration test, not with the trade. If the spread isn't stationary, no position-sizing rule will save it. Project 05 is the pre-trade filter for projects 02 and 06.",
    formula: '\\text{ADF} = -2.11 \\;\\not<\\; -2.86_{5\\%}',
  },
  {
    id: 'M04',
    title: 'Fade-funding trade IS Sharpe 1.11. OOS Sharpe −0.05. Alpha decayed post-2023.',
    project: 'Project 06 — Crypto funding carry',
    date: '2026-04-05',
    severity: 'medium',
    summary:
      'The textbook perpetual-swap carry trade is to fade funding (short when funding > 0). IS Sharpe was 1.11. OOS Sharpe was −0.05. The carry was real (+11.9% annualized), but the trade that captured it was systematically arbitraged away as the participant mix shifted.',
    caught_by: 'G11–G15 (locked OOS windows, 5-era stability)',
    repair:
      'The OOS window was locked before data was touched. The decay was visible in the rolling OOS-Sharpe trace — Sharpe 1.11 → 0.91 → 0.71 → 0.42 → 0.04 → −0.05 over the rolling window. The "carry is real, trade is dead" conclusion was honest.',
    lesson:
      'Carry signals are observable, regularly-paid, and visible to anyone with the data — which means they crowd fast. Pre-registering the OOS window before touching the data is what makes this a study and not a justification.',
    formula: '\\mathrm{IS} \\neq \\mathrm{OOS} \\;\\Rightarrow\\; \\alpha \\text{ decayed}',
  },
  {
    id: 'M05',
    title: 'First DSR pass on project 01: forgot γ₃·SR̂ term. Decoy result.',
    project: 'Project 01 — Multiple testing / deflated Sharpe',
    date: '2025-09-20',
    severity: 'low',
    summary:
      "When implementing the Deflated Sharpe Ratio from the Bailey & López de Prado 2014 paper, I first wrote the simpler form: DSR = (SR̂ − E[max SR]) / σ_SR̂. The paper's full form has the higher-moment correction: (1 − γ₃·SR̂ + (γ₄·SR̂² − 1)/4) under the radical. Without it, returns with non-zero skew/kurtosis inflate the denominator and DSR is overstated.",
    caught_by: 'G6–G10 (parameter-prior sensitivity, Monte-Carlo coverage)',
    repair:
      "Re-derived the formula from the paper's full expression. Added γ₃ and γ₄ to the calculator inputs as defaults (0, 3) with a comment that real-data estimates are recommended. The interactive DSR calculator on /methodology ships the full form.",
    lesson:
      'When the paper gives you a higher-moment correction, the higher-moment correction is the paper. The simplified form is for textbook examples. Always read the equation, never paraphrase it from a Stack Overflow answer.',
    formula:
      '\\mathrm{DSR} = \\frac{\\widehat{\\mathrm{SR}} - \\mathrm{SR}_0}{\\sigma_{\\hat{SR}} \\sqrt{1 - \\gamma_3 \\cdot \\widehat{\\mathrm{SR}} + \\gamma_4 \\cdot \\frac{\\widehat{\\mathrm{SR}}^2 - 1}{4}}}',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="What I got wrong"
  description="Postmortems of failed strategies, broken gates, and pipeline bugs. A researcher's failures are more diagnostic than their wins."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Home', href: '/' },
    { name: 'Mistakes', href: '/mistakes' },
  ]}
>
  <header class="mistakes-head">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section__eyebrow"><span class="mono">mistakes/</span> · public postmortems</p>
      <h1 class="mistakes-head__title">
        What I <span class="hl">got wrong</span>.
      </h1>
      <VoiceLine class="mistakes-head__voice">
        A book of {quantProjectCount} winners with no postmortems is a book primed for selection bias.
      </VoiceLine>
      <p class="mistakes-head__sub">
        A research book that ships {quantProjectCount} winners and hides the failure modes is a book primed
        for selection bias. Below are five real failures from the quant pipeline — what was wrong, which
        gate caught it, what I repaired, and what the discipline is for. NDA-safe. Public data.
      </p>

      <div class="mistakes-head__eq-block">
        <Equation
          block
          size="md"
          latex={`\\text{book\\_quality} = \\min\\!\\left(\\text{wins},\\; \\text{postmortems}\\right)`}
        />
        <p class="mistakes-head__eq-caption">
          A book is only as honest as its weakest postmortem. The minimum of wins and postmortems is
          the binding constraint.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <ol class="mistakes-list">
        {
          mistakes.map((m) => (
            <li class={`mistake severity--${m.severity}`}>
              <header class="mistake__head">
                <div class="mistake__id mono">{m.id}</div>
                <div class="mistake__meta">
                  <div class="mistake__project mono">{m.project}</div>
                  <div class="mistake__date mono">{m.date}</div>
                </div>
                <div class={`mistake__severity severity-tag--${m.severity} mono`}>{m.severity}</div>
              </header>

              <h2 class="mistake__title">{m.title}</h2>

              <div class="mistake__formula">
                <Equation latex={m.formula} size="sm" />
              </div>

              <div class="mistake__grid">
                <div class="mistake__row">
                  <div class="mistake__row-label mono">What was wrong</div>
                  <p class="mistake__row-body">{m.summary}</p>
                </div>
                <div class="mistake__row">
                  <div class="mistake__row-label mono">Which gate caught it</div>
                  <p class="mistake__row-body">
                    <span class="mistake__gate-pill">{m.caught_by}</span>
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="mistake__row">
                  <div class="mistake__row-label mono">Repair</div>
                  <p class="mistake__row-body">{m.repair}</p>
                </div>
                <div class="mistake__row">
                  <div class="mistake__row-label mono">Lesson</div>
                  <p class="mistake__row-body mistake__lesson">{m.lesson}</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section__head">
        <p class="section__eyebrow">What this page is not</p>
        <h2 class="section__title">Negative space as design.</h2>
        <p class="section__sub">
          This page is not self-flagellation, and it is not a humility performance. It is a record
          of the failure modes the gate stack is built to catch. If a gate didn't catch the failure,
          the gate gets updated; the failure gets logged. There is no "we'll be more careful next
          time" — there is a pre-ship test.
        </p>
      </header>
      <ul class="neg">
        <li>
          I am not above shipping a 5.07 phantom Sharpe — that is exactly the failure mode the gates
          exist to prevent.
        </li>
        <li>
          I am not claiming the gate stack catches everything — there are {profile.stats.evalGates} gates
          and they fail closed on the obvious ones; the subtle ones come later.
        </li>
        <li>
          I am not hiding any failures that I am aware of — if a postmortem would change your
          hire/no-hire, it is on this page.
        </li>
        <li>
          I am not interested in "fake failure" stories — these are real failures from the actual
          pipeline, with the actual numbers.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABanner
    title="Want the failure log for a specific strategy?"
    sub={`If you have a written spec, send it. I'll send back which of ${GATE_RANGE} already apply to your stack, which ones would catch your last failure, and which I'd build.`}
    primaryLabel="Email me"
    secondaryLabel="Read methodology"
    secondaryHref={path('/methodology')}
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .mistakes-head {
    padding-block: var(--sp-9) var(--sp-7);
    background: var(--c-bg);
    border-bottom: var(--border);
  }
  .mistakes-head__title {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin-block: var(--sp-4) var(--sp-5);
    max-width: 22ch;
  }
  .mistakes-head__sub {
    font-size: var(--fs-lg);
    color: var(--c-ink-2);
    line-height: var(--lh-loose);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-7);
  }
  .mistakes-head__voice {
    margin: 0 0 var(--sp-5);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .mistakes-head__eq-block {
    padding: var(--sp-5);
    background: var(--c-paper);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    overflow-x: auto;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--c-primary-2);
  }
  .mistakes-head__eq-caption {
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--c-ink-2);
    line-height: var(--lh-loose);
    margin-top: var(--sp-3);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .mistakes-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-6);
  }

  .mistake {
    background: var(--c-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: var(--sp-6);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--c-primary-2);
    transition: border-color var(--transition);
  }
  .mistake:hover {
    border-color: var(--c-primary);
  }
  /* v6.11.10 — F14 amber-only. Critical severity now ink-2 (no red). */
  .severity--critical {
    border-left-color: var(--c-ink-2);
  }
  .severity--high {
    border-left-color: #c98a16;
  }
  .severity--medium {
    border-left-color: var(--c-primary-2-deep);
  }
  .severity--low {
    border-left-color: var(--c-primary);
  }

  .mistake__head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--sp-4);
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .mistake__id {
    font-size: var(--fs-xl);
    color: var(--c-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .mistake__meta {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 200px;
  }
  .mistake__project {
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--c-ink);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .mistake__date {
    font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    color: var(--c-ink-3);
    margin-top: 2px;
  }
  .mistake__severity {
    font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .severity-tag--critical {
    background: color-mix(in oklab, var(--c-amber) 0.18%, transparent);
    color: var(--c-primary-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-primary-2);
  }
  .severity-tag--high {
    background: var(--c-amberl-mist);
    color: var(--c-primary-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-amberl-mid);
  }
  .severity-tag--medium {
    background: var(--c-amberl-faint);
    color: var(--c-primary-2-deep);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-amberl-decor);
  }
  .severity-tag--low {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--c-ink-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
  }

  .mistake__title {
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2vw, 1.625rem);
    line-height: 1.25;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-4);
    color: var(--c-ink);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .mistake__formula {
    margin-block: var(--sp-3) var(--sp-5);
    padding: var(--sp-3) var(--sp-4);
    background: var(--c-paper);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-rule-soft);
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .mistake__grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-4);
    margin-top: var(--sp-4);
  }
  .mistake__row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr;
    gap: var(--sp-4);
    padding-block: var(--sp-3);
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--c-rule-soft);
  }
  .mistake__row:first-child {
    border-top: none;
  }
  .mistake__row-label {
    font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    color: var(--c-ink-3);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding-top: 2px;
  }
  .mistake__row-body {
    font-size: var(--fs-base);
    color: var(--c-ink);
    line-height: var(--lh-loose);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .mistake__gate-pill {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    background: var(--c-bg-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-rule);
    border-radius: 14px;
    font-family: var(--ff-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-xs);
    color: var(--c-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .mistake__lesson {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--c-ink-2);
    padding-left: var(--sp-3);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--c-primary-2);
  }

  .neg {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .neg li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--sp-3);
    line-height: var(--lh-loose);
    color: var(--c-ink-2);
    font-size: var(--fs-base);
  }
  .neg li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.6em;
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--c-ink-3);
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .mistake__row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--sp-1);
    }
    .mistake {
      padding: var(--sp-4);
    }
    .mistake__head {
      gap: var(--sp-3);
    }
  }
</style>
